                              <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                                Recently, the term “self-love” has blown up on the internet and garnered massive attention. People have been talking about practising self-love on social media platforms, YouTube videos, websites and even music videos. Most of us find it extremely hard to accept ourselves for who we are and love ourselves. I’m here to tell you that it is okay to feel so. You don’t have to feel burdened to love every aspect of yourself; however, you can implement a few practices to slowly start making peace with yourself over time. A few practices that you can adopt to begin your self-love and acceptance journey are:

                                </p>
                                <p>
                                <ul style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';"><li>●	Gain a Realistic Perspective on Self-Love </li>
                                  <li>● Let Go of the Past </li>
                                  <li>●	Value Your Self-Respect </li>
                                  <li>●	Declutter Your Head-Space </li>
                                  <li>●	Don’t Compare Yourself to Anyone Else  </li>
                                  <li>●	Own Your Body With Pride </li>
                                  <li>●	Compliment Yourself </li>
                                  <li>●	Allow Yourself to Feel Low </li>
                                   
                                  	</ul> 
                                  
                              </p>
                               
                             

                        <H3 style=" font-style: underline">1. <u>Gain a Realistic Perspective on Self-Love: 
                        </u>
                        </H3>
                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            To begin with, you need to understand the real picture of what a self-love journey looks like. Realistically speaking, self-love is not just about aromatic candles or luxurious skincare. There’s nothing wrong with indulging in candles and skincare, but the point is that self-love exceeds these things. Loving yourself is a journey that has its own difficulties and is a time-consuming process. 
                        </p>
                        <H3 style=" font-style: underline">2. <u>Forgive Yourself for Your Mistakes:
                        </u>
                        </H3>
                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            Everyone makes mistakes in life, and it is only human to do so. The problem arises when we hold onto our mistakes and punish ourselves for them. Learn from your mistakes, take your lesson and ensure you don’t repeat the same mistakes. Growth has its own share of failures and downfalls, so allow yourself to make mistakes, forgive yourself and rise again. 

                        </p>
                   
                        <div class="row" >
                            <div class="col-lg-12 col-12" style="padding: 0 0 0 0;" >
                                <img alt="Love yourself" class="blogimg" src="https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/waves-36bb5.appspot.com/o/website%20blog%20photos%2Fself_Love_blog%2F3791761.jpg?alt=media&token=b762afe0-ad56-4bf0-b534-c86f74592e7c" >
                            </div>
                            </div>

                            <H3 style=" font-style: underline">3. <u>Let Go of the Past: 
                            </u>
                            </H3>
                            
                            <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                                Getting over the burden of the past- the trauma, regrets and unpleasant experiences associated with it is not easy but necessary. Dwelling on a bygone time will keep you bound to your past. You must liberate yourself from the burden of the past and let it go. Instead, focus on making your present better and brighter. Focus on yourself at this very moment.
                            </p>

                            <H3 style=" font-style: underline">4. <u>Value Your Self-Respect 
                            </u>
                            </H3>
                            <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                                This is one of the most significant aspects that you need to prioritise. If you don’t respect yourself, no one will. You need to value yourself. Being humble and polite is great; however, it is pivotal to not confuse politeness with being a pushover. Set boundaries where you need to and confront people affirmatively when they attempt to trample you or bring you down. Remember, protecting your self-respect is not vanity; it is a necessity.
                            </p>
                            <div class="row" >
                              <div class="col-lg-12 col-12" style="padding: 0 0 0 0;" >
                                  <img alt="How to stay strong" class="blogimg" src="https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/waves-36bb5.appspot.com/o/website%20blog%20photos%2Fself_Love_blog%2F5574182.jpg?alt=media&token=833b64b4-8c41-405a-811a-5466be2af44e" >
                              </div>
                              </div>
  <br>
                            <H3 style=" font-style: underline">5. <u>Declutter Your Head-Space:
                            </u>
                            </H3>
                            <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                                Bringing your mind to peace is essential to ensure you can practice self-love with tranquillity. Though it is not as easy as it sounds, one cannot deny how important it is to clear your mind of pessimistic thoughts. You need to believe and have faith in yourself and your abilities. Practice substituting self-doubt with self-confidence and faith. 
  </p>

                                <H3 style=" font-style: underline">6. <u>Don’t Compare Yourself to Anyone Else:
                                </u>
                                </H3>
                                <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                                    Picture perfect models on hoardings and banners, seemingly perfect people on social media and actors and people around us often seem too good to be true. We compare our ‘flaws’ to their ‘perfections’ which makes us seep into a vicious cycle of inferiority complex. Unwinding yourself from such thoughts and putting an end to the comparisons you make between yourself and others is crucial. No one is exactly the same as you, so cherish your unique self. 
                                </p>
                                <H3 style=" font-style: underline">7. <u>Own Your Body with Pride:
                                </u>
                                
      <br>
                                </H3>
                                <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                                    Media has played an enormous role in embedding the idea of a “perfect body” or a “perfect physique” in our minds. But in reality, beauty comes in all shapes, sizes and genders. Building a good relationship with one’s body and accepting it wholly is essential to one’s self-love journey. Be proud of your favourite features. Flaunt them if you like. If you love your hair, take care of it and be proud of it. The features that seem like “flaws” to you are what make you real and humane. Find beauty in your scars and marks and own them with pride.  </p>
                                
                                </p>
                                <div class="row" >
                                  <div class="col-lg-12 col-12" style="padding: 0 0 0 0;" >
                                      <img alt="How to stay body positive" class="blogimg" src="https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/waves-36bb5.appspot.com/o/website%20blog%20photos%2Fself_Love_blog%2F10085.jpg?alt=media&token=e54da931-837e-4a06-bd37-f0ae33577579" >
                                  </div>
                                  </div>
                                    <H3 style=" font-style: underline">8. <u>Compliment Yourself:
                                </u>
                                </H3>
                                <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                                    Acknowledging and appreciating your strengths is vital to boosting your self-confidence. Compliment yourself for the things you like about yourself. Celebrate your wins and achievements- regardless of big or small, they are. You need not do it out loud and can keep it to yourself. Telling yourself, “Well done”, “I’m proud of me”, “I got this,” and such uplifting statements in your mind is all it takes. You can even buy small treats (ice-creams/sweets/anything you like) to celebrate your wins. Don’t wait for someone to compliment you. You can brighten your day by complimenting yourself. 
  </p>

  <H3 style=" font-style: underline">9. <u>Allow Yourself to Feel Low:
</u>
</H3>
<p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
    Your self-love journey might not always be happiness, sunshine and flowers. You might go through rough patches in accepting yourself, learning to undo negative self-criticism, and loving yourself. You might feel low, burnt out and even exhausted. Don’t take yourself down a guilt trip when you feel hurt or vulnerable. Confronting and negotiating these negative feelings is not bad at all. It would help you cleanse all your bottled-up feelings and be a cathartic experience. 
</p>

<p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">Last but not least, everyone’s self-love journey looks different. So don’t compare your journey towards practising self-love with anyone else’s. Take your own time to let go of all negative thoughts and emotions and welcome optimistic and uplifting ones. It is okay to resist the process, but have faith in it, and you will eventually get better at accepting yourself and making peace with your existence. When it gets too hard to love yourself, imagine how you would want someone to adore, cherish and love you. Treat yourself exactly like that because you deserve every bit of it! 
</p>




